e light-activated rhodopsin state were likely maintained through intensified constraint after bats diversified, being finely tuned in response to novel sensory specializations. Our study demonstrates the power of combining experimental and computational approaches for investigating functional mechanisms underlying the evolution of complex sensory adaptations.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Gutierrez, Eduardo De A", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Castiglione, Gianni M", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Morrow, James M", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Schott, Ryan K", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Loureiro, Livia O", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lim, Burton K", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Chang, Belinda S W", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "O'Connell, Mary", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/f58f8618b2fae353a37ba9fff6b2feb2", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/bee5ed37a68b3c6cbf7568917451014c28107aa1c1767db72eb3fda71a9a8882", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/HW4TDLNN", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/HW4TDLNN", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/9ed6f6930523661357fab1f93fcf3dba!/b315954-318426", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"},